  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Overview"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "App Shortcuts provide a polished experience for your app intents and entities in the"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Shortcuts app and other system experiences. An App Shortcut combines the action from your"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "text": "app intent with other data, such as a title, image, and spoken phrases that someone might",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "use to run the shortcut. A shortcut can also contain preconfigured parameters, so someone",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "can run the action quickly, and without having to specify additional information. For example,"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "a hiking app might offer an app intent to start a hike, but require you to select a trail"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "before starting the action. Without a shortcut, someone must provide the trail information"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "each time they run the intent. However, a shortcut can simplify this flow by offering to"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "start a hike on the person’s favorite trail."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You create App Shortcuts programmatically in your code, and the compiler generates the information",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "the rest of the system needs to use it. This approach means that the shortcuts you create"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "are available as soon as someone installs your app, and you don’t have to register them yourself.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Specify your shortcuts in your code by defining a custom type that adopts the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AppShortcutsProvider",
              "isActive": true
            },
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "protocol. Include this type in your app, app extension, Swift package, or library that you"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "use to manage your intents-related code. Inside this type, construct one or more "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AppShortcut",
              "isActive": true
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "text": "types using static data. Define your shortcuts in the same place you define the app intents",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "that those shortcuts use."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "style": "note",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Apple may extract anonymized App Shortcuts data such as localized phrases, display"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "representation values, and the title and description of related intents. Machine learning"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "models use this data when training to help improve the App Shortcuts experience."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Although the Shortcuts app and other system features find your shortcuts automatically, you can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "text": "also make them available from your app using tip views. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference",
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/SiriTipView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/SiriTipUIView",
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "text": "types display the relevant shortcuts for the app intent you specify. You can also use a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/ShortcutsLink",
              "isActive": true
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/ShortcutsUIButton"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to open your app’s page in the Shortcuts app."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
